but she didn't at all.

1006
01:37:00,400 --> 01:37:02,400
I think there's gonna be trouble
with the chums.

1007
01:37:04,952 --> 01:37:08,300
Maybe some people don't like
being double-crossed.

1008
01:37:08,600 --> 01:37:10,958
Well, we've got to
look after ourselves.

1009
01:37:28,009 --> 01:37:28,910
Maisie!

1010
01:37:31,813 --> 01:37:32,980
Here you are at last.

1011
01:37:33,981 --> 01:37:35,283
I've been looking
everywhere for you.

1012
01:37:36,150 --> 01:37:38,686
Have you? I've been
for a bathe with Fay.

1013
01:37:39,287 --> 01:37:41,500
Are you sure there wasn't
anybody else with you?

1014
01:37:41,900 --> 01:37:42,723
What if there was?

1015
01:37:43,691 --> 01:37:46,861
I can go bathing
with whom I choose.

1016
01:37:46,861 --> 01:37:48,329
I wished you choose me.

1017
01:37:49,163 --> 01:37:52,567
You are just a boy.
Maybe I want someone more mature.

1018
01:37:53,768 --> 01:37:55,169
Say your right lines
or shut up.

1019
01:37:56,871 --> 01:37:57,839
But Maisie, why?

1020
01:37:58,840 --> 01:38:01,800
Because I want to have
a good time while I'm young.

1021
01:38:02,500 --> 01:38:05,880
After all I'm only 17.

1022
01:38:07,515 --> 01:38:09,016
But I can show you a good time.

1023
01:38:09,717 --> 01:38:11,552
It's not as if I hadn't got
plenty of cash.

1024
01:38:11,986 --> 01:38:13,154
Money isn't everything

1025
01:38:13,721 --> 01:38:15,400
though it certainly helps.

1026
01:38:16,000 --> 01:38:18,800
One more "ad lib" like that, toots,
